Date of Birth: February 6, 1886<br/>
Birthplace: Farmington, Utah, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: April 16, 1952<br/>
Death: January 11, 1983<br/>
<br/>
Born Feb. 6, 1886, at Farmington, Davis Co., Utah, to George Franklin Richards and Alice Almira Robinson.
Sustained Presiding Bishop of the Church April 6, 1938, at age 52;
ordained apostle April 16, 1952, by David 0. McKay, at age 66; died Jan. 11, 1983, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 96.